RoleDescription:
Your contribution to something big:-  Support in cost analysis of products and support in preparation of annual price negotiation with suppliers;
- Support in supplier management &amp; supplier strategy (supplier development or consolidation) formulation;
- Support operative and strategic purchasing processes;
- Development of improvement measures together with the responsible buyers;
- Support commercial buyers on daily tasks.What distinguishes you: - Degree and/or Master's Degree in the fields of Engineering, Management, Economy, International Relations or similar;
- Advanced level of English;
- Good communication skills (Portuguese and English);
- Strong analytical competences and results orientated attitude;
- Experience/knowledge in Microsoft Excel is mandatory;
- Knowledge of SAP is a plus, but not mandatory;
- Ability to work as a team in a dynamic environment and to contribute for the collective success.Work #LikeABosch includes:  Flexible work conditions Hybrid work system Exchange with colleagues around the world Medical office on site (psychology and general clinic) Training opportunities (p.e., technical training, foreign languages training) &amp; certifications Professional development Access to great discounts in partnerships and Bosch products Sports and health related activities Great access to public transports Free transport from Porto Free parking lot Canteen Success stories don t just happen. They are made...Make it happen. We are looking forward to your application!
